## Coding Workflow

Transcripts are coded, then reviewed. Run in order:

1. `/data-tagging` — codes the transcript; saves `outputs/analysis/transcript-N-tags.md`
2. `/data-reviewing` — reviews tagged outputs in `outputs/analysis/`; saves `outputs/reviews/transcript-N-review.md`
3. Researcher adjudicates and approves flagged changes
4. `/data-reviewing` (post-approval) — applies approved changes; saves modified files to `outputs/modified/`, generates `outputs/modified/code-table.md` and `outputs/modified/code-table.html`

## Skills Quick Reference

| Command | What It Does |
|---------|-------------|
| `/data-tagging` | Codes a transcript → `outputs/analysis/transcript-N-tags.md` |
| `/data-reviewing` | Reviews tagged outputs → `outputs/reviews/transcript-N-review.md`; after approval, saves corrected files + code table + visualization to `outputs/modified/` |

